1
00:00:05,105 --> 00:00:06,473
Don't screw with me.

2
00:00:07,140 --> 00:00:09,376
Why did you just go and die on your own?

3
00:00:09,442 --> 00:00:12,278
If you're going to die,
tell us everything first.

4
00:00:12,345 --> 00:00:15,015
<i>Someone related to him</i>
<i>might know something.</i>

5
00:00:15,582 --> 00:00:17,050
<i>There must be a clue somewhere.</i>

6
00:00:19,652 --> 00:00:21,187
Is it a phone number?

7
00:00:23,890 --> 00:00:24,924
Hello.

8
00:00:24,991 --> 00:00:26,726
<i>Who is this?</i>

9
00:00:30,463 --> 00:00:31,831
Why are you picking up, Fumi…

10
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:35,502
BREATHING MOUNTAINS
FUMI KARASHIMA PHOTO EXHIBIT

11
00:00:36,269 --> 00:00:37,237
Wait,

12
00:00:38,371 --> 00:00:39,506
are you Makoto?

13
00:00:40,173 --> 00:00:41,074
<i>Yes.</i>

14
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:44,677
There’s something I want to ask.
Can we meet somewhere?

15
00:00:51,017 --> 00:00:53,253
Why are those two connected?

16
00:00:54,487 --> 00:00:56,189
We'll have to ask her directly.

17
00:00:57,023 --> 00:00:59,225
Maybe she even knows Tsuda’s motive.

18
00:01:00,460 --> 00:01:02,529
Is that key the only clue left?

19
00:01:07,167 --> 00:01:08,501
Hand it over.

20
00:01:08,568 --> 00:01:10,470
What you just put in your pocket.

21
00:01:13,306 --> 00:01:18,645
The Violent Crimes Division will keep that
until the bereaved family is located.

22
00:01:19,345 --> 00:01:22,649
Take it without permission and
you'll be subject to disciplinary action.

23
00:01:27,287 --> 00:01:28,721
Don't do it.

24
00:01:28,788 --> 00:01:31,357
Searching any further is useless.

25
00:01:33,026 --> 00:01:34,027
Tsuda

26
00:01:35,395 --> 00:01:37,530
didn't kill your parents.

27
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:40,934
What?

28
00:01:41,734 --> 00:01:43,002
How do you know that?

29
00:01:48,608 --> 00:01:50,210
I never thought you brothers

30
00:01:52,178 --> 00:01:54,881
would end up becoming police officers.

31
00:01:57,083 --> 00:02:00,653
I used to be in the prefectural
police's First Division.

32
00:02:02,155 --> 00:02:03,022
First Division?

33
00:02:04,924 --> 00:02:05,859
No way…

34
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:09,028
I was chasing that case.

35
00:02:09,696 --> 00:02:12,098
<i>When will you catch them?</i>

36
00:02:12,866 --> 00:02:15,368
Why did my mom and dad die?

37
00:02:15,435 --> 00:02:20,340
1996

38
00:02:23,076 --> 00:02:25,011
You two were young back then.

39
00:02:27,347 --> 00:02:29,782
It's no wonder you didn't notice.

40
00:02:31,885 --> 00:02:33,386
<i>Did you catch the killer?</i>

41
00:02:33,953 --> 00:02:38,258
I looked into it,
but it wasn't that person.

42
00:02:38,324 --> 00:02:39,159
What?

43
00:02:39,225 --> 00:02:41,361
1995

44
00:02:41,427 --> 00:02:43,897
But we, the police,

45
00:02:44,464 --> 00:02:48,535
will definitely catch the culprit.

46
00:03:08,188 --> 00:03:09,522
That night,

47
00:03:10,156 --> 00:03:13,226
Tsuda was called out
by someone from a publishing company

48
00:03:13,293 --> 00:03:15,995
and was drinking at a pub in Jimbocho.

49
00:03:16,896 --> 00:03:18,331
Maybe he faked an alibi?

50
00:03:18,398 --> 00:03:20,567
He said he would come
to our house that night.

51
00:03:20,633 --> 00:03:23,369
He was caught on a security camera.

52
00:03:23,436 --> 00:03:26,306
But the records back then
didn't mention it…

53
00:03:27,106 --> 00:03:30,343
A politician the Second Division
was tailing also appeared in that footage.

54
00:03:32,278 --> 00:03:33,913
To prevent it from leaking,

55
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:40,453
the higher-ups decided not to report it
and just kept it an internal issue.

56
00:03:43,022 --> 00:03:46,759
I never imagined you guys
were still chasing Tsuda.

57
00:03:46,826 --> 00:03:49,495
If that's the case, why did he run away?

58
00:03:49,562 --> 00:03:51,864
If he’s innocent,
he had no need to disappear.

59
00:03:51,931 --> 00:03:54,033
He was removed from the list of suspects.

60
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:56,135
You know the police
didn't look further into him.

61
00:03:58,605 --> 00:04:01,941
Is there anything else
you know about Tsuda?

62
00:04:04,677 --> 00:04:05,712
Mr. Koike!

63
00:04:09,549 --> 00:04:10,617
Tsuda

64
00:04:11,851 --> 00:04:16,389
might have been interviewing
people other than your father.

65
00:04:18,057 --> 00:04:19,492
Other people?

66
00:04:21,961 --> 00:04:24,130
The factory where the fire happened.

67
00:04:24,197 --> 00:04:26,099
1995, APRIL 26

68
00:04:26,165 --> 00:04:28,601
<i>Apparently, he was sniffing</i>
<i>around that area.</i>

69
00:04:30,203 --> 00:04:33,406
I don't think it is relevant
to the case, though.

70
00:04:35,775 --> 00:04:36,676
Give it.

71
00:04:38,811 --> 00:04:39,779
The key.

72
00:04:48,421 --> 00:04:50,523
-Help us out here.
-What?

73
00:04:50,590 --> 00:04:52,859
If there's a similar key,
they won't notice.

74
00:04:52,925 --> 00:04:54,427
What are you guys--

75
00:04:54,494 --> 00:04:55,995
At least do that much for us.

76
00:04:56,696 --> 00:04:58,965
Since you didn't do anything
for us back then.

77
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:03,569
The statute of limitations expired.

78
00:05:05,838 --> 00:05:08,241
What’s the point
of finding the culprit now?

79
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:09,809
We want to know.

80
00:05:11,811 --> 00:05:13,880
Why were our parents killed?

81
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:21,020
We won't cause you any more trouble.

82
00:05:24,057 --> 00:05:29,028
LAND FOR LEASE AS CAR PARK, STORAGE, ETC.

83
00:05:29,095 --> 00:05:32,865
If he was investigating the factory,
that explains why he knows Fumi.

84
00:05:33,599 --> 00:05:36,035
What was Tsuda investigating?

85
00:05:40,139 --> 00:05:43,242
Seems after the fire,
the land here was sold off.

86
00:05:44,644 --> 00:05:48,047
But it’s not like everything is gone.

87
00:05:49,349 --> 00:05:51,017
If it’s not Tsuda,

88
00:05:53,052 --> 00:05:55,488
the culprit is still out there somewhere.

89
00:06:05,765 --> 00:06:08,768
<i>I'm Kawano from the Akita Police.</i>
<i>Please, go ahead.</i>

90
00:06:09,802 --> 00:06:10,937
Let’s get started then.

91
00:06:12,004 --> 00:06:14,440
Resident Aiko Mizusawa
was killed in an arson-murder

92
00:06:14,507 --> 00:06:16,409
at her apartment in the Kanagawa Ward.

93
00:06:16,476 --> 00:06:20,179
Gold bars worth 100 million yen
were found in the residence.

94
00:06:20,246 --> 00:06:23,816
After verification,
they matched the gold bars

95
00:06:23,883 --> 00:06:27,286
from the 400 million yen robbery
that occurred in Akita a year ago.

96
00:06:27,353 --> 00:06:28,855
There were four robbers.

97
00:06:28,921 --> 00:06:32,725
Was Aiko Mizusawa's name
on the suspect list?

98
00:06:32,792 --> 00:06:36,329
<i>No, she wasn't listed here.</i>

99
00:06:36,396 --> 00:06:38,631
There's testimony that before her death,

100
00:06:38,698 --> 00:06:42,335
Mizusawa was being stalked
by a man named Togo.

101
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:46,305
He is thought to be either
one of the robbers, or the mastermind.

102
00:06:46,372 --> 00:06:48,975
Do you have any information on him?

103
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:52,278
<i>We have no information at this time.</i>

104
00:06:53,112 --> 00:06:56,516
<i>Are you saying that</i>
<i>this Togo man is the arsonist?</i>

105
00:06:56,582 --> 00:06:59,619
No, the one who set the fire
is likely Yugo Hiranaka.

106
00:07:00,353 --> 00:07:02,088
<i>Yugo Hiranaka?</i>

107
00:07:02,622 --> 00:07:04,090
Flyers used to start the fire

108
00:07:04,157 --> 00:07:06,793
were only distributed around
where Hiranaka lives.

109
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:09,796
Hiranaka also had a bruise on his neck

110
00:07:09,862 --> 00:07:12,765
that closely resembled the tattoo
of one of the four robbers.

111
00:07:12,832 --> 00:07:17,069
Hiranaka and Togo might have been
chasing Mizusawa together.

112
00:07:17,737 --> 00:07:20,706
However, Hiranaka fled by car.

113
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:22,575
<i>We are currently tracking him.</i>

114
00:07:25,912 --> 00:07:28,514
Did Hiranaka flee in a panic?

115
00:07:28,581 --> 00:07:31,584
His smartphone is turned off, right?

116
00:07:31,651 --> 00:07:32,585
Yes.

117
00:07:32,652 --> 00:07:35,388
It’s difficult to pinpoint his location
via cell signal.

118
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:37,824
He lives in a nice house.

119
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:44,430
Yes.

120
00:07:45,498 --> 00:07:46,399
Right.

121
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:54,607
Do you think he left and met up with Togo?

122
00:07:54,674 --> 00:07:56,642
They’re probably overseas by now.

123
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:58,578
Such shallow logic.

124
00:07:59,779 --> 00:08:00,813
-What?
-Oh, no.

125
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:02,748
-What did you just say?
-That hurts.

126
00:08:02,815 --> 00:08:03,950
-I'm sorry.
-Hey.

127
00:08:04,016 --> 00:08:05,151
Hey.

128
00:08:06,652 --> 00:08:08,488
They found

129
00:08:09,922 --> 00:08:11,290
Yugo Hiranaka's body.

130
00:08:12,592 --> 00:08:13,459
What?

131
00:08:16,028 --> 00:08:17,830
One, two, three.

132
00:08:19,265 --> 00:08:20,199
There.

133
00:08:20,266 --> 00:08:21,801
-Scale.
-Here.

134
00:08:22,835 --> 00:08:26,806
Nine stab wounds were confirmed
on the back of the body.

135
00:08:27,540 --> 00:08:31,644
The fatal wound was a stab
below the right shoulder blade.

136
00:08:32,311 --> 00:08:36,182
The blade pierced the lungs,
causing air and blood to fill the chest.

137
00:08:36,249 --> 00:08:38,918
The culprit must have had a strong grudge.

138
00:08:39,685 --> 00:08:41,153
Dr. Kagura.

139
00:08:41,220 --> 00:08:43,556
There’s a variation
in the depth of the wounds.

140
00:08:44,290 --> 00:08:47,627
They range from six centimeters
to 14 centimeters at the deepest.

141
00:08:48,661 --> 00:08:50,029
What about the angle?

142
00:08:50,830 --> 00:08:52,565
The blade was inserted like this…

143
00:08:53,232 --> 00:08:54,333
Almost vertically.

144
00:08:56,269 --> 00:08:57,436
I see.

145
00:09:09,682 --> 00:09:11,217
What’s bothering you?

146
00:09:11,717 --> 00:09:13,085
The force of the stabs.

147
00:09:13,686 --> 00:09:17,323
If there’s a strong intent to kill,
the blade is usually plunged in deep.

148
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:20,059
But the body had several
shallow wounds as well.

149
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:23,095
-In cases like this…
-They were probably in a hurry.

150
00:09:23,829 --> 00:09:25,865
Maybe someone was coming.

151
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:29,035
Repeated stabbing in a short time?

152
00:09:29,101 --> 00:09:32,204
Repeated stabbing would cause
the depth of the wounds to vary.

153
00:09:35,608 --> 00:09:39,545
The man killed at the marina
is Yugo Hiranaka, 23 years old.

154
00:09:39,612 --> 00:09:42,682
An investor who owns several
properties within the prefecture.

155
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:46,118
His legal residence was Akita Prefecture,
the same as Aiko Mizusawa.

156
00:09:46,886 --> 00:09:49,322
Hiranaka suffered neglect as a child

157
00:09:49,388 --> 00:09:51,591
and was reportedly estranged
from his parents.

158
00:09:51,657 --> 00:09:54,427
This photo was found at his home.

159
00:09:54,493 --> 00:09:56,195
It also shows Aiko Mizusawa

160
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:59,599
and a person believed
to be her friend, Saki Yokokura.

161
00:09:59,665 --> 00:10:03,302
Hiranaka started investing one year ago,

162
00:10:03,369 --> 00:10:06,038
immediately after the gold robbery.

163
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:08,007
Like Aiko Mizusawa,

164
00:10:08,541 --> 00:10:12,878
Hiranaka may have used
the gold bars he made off with.

165
00:10:13,412 --> 00:10:14,447
The autopsy results?

166
00:10:15,014 --> 00:10:18,918
On Yugo Hiranaka's body,
we found no defensive wounds.

167
00:10:18,985 --> 00:10:21,020
Does that mean he knew the suspect?

168
00:10:21,587 --> 00:10:23,122
We don't know that yet.

169
00:10:23,723 --> 00:10:26,792
The moment of the crime
was not caught on security cameras,

170
00:10:26,859 --> 00:10:28,628
but a person carrying a suitcase

171
00:10:28,694 --> 00:10:31,497
was sighted near the marina
at the same time.

172
00:10:32,164 --> 00:10:33,866
Is this man Togo?

173
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:36,969
The motive for the crime
was likely the suitcase.

174
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:40,406
The case the man is holding
belonged to Hiranaka.

175
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:45,011
The contents might be
the rest of the gold bars.

176
00:10:45,077 --> 00:10:47,647
It's possible they had
a falling out, and he took it.

177
00:10:48,614 --> 00:10:50,383
The robbers were a group of four.

178
00:10:50,449 --> 00:10:53,386
It's hard to believe
it’s just a coincidence.

179
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:57,790
It's possible this Yuzuru boy's
family name is Togo.

180
00:10:57,857 --> 00:11:00,893
Continue to search for witnesses, and…

181
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:04,196
investigate Saki Yokokura
as a person of interest.

182
00:11:04,263 --> 00:11:05,431
Yes, sir!

183
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:10,436
BATHHOUSE

184
00:11:11,370 --> 00:11:13,272
This place hasn't changed.

185
00:11:14,407 --> 00:11:16,475
Man, I'm hungry.

186
00:11:18,444 --> 00:11:19,578
But…

187
00:11:19,645 --> 00:11:21,647
I just don't get it.

188
00:11:21,714 --> 00:11:22,782
Get what?

189
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:24,583
Why Hiranaka

190
00:11:24,650 --> 00:11:28,187
went as far as to set fire to the house
of his childhood friend, Aiko Mizusawa.

191
00:11:28,954 --> 00:11:30,022
Hey.

192
00:11:30,089 --> 00:11:31,957
I'm off the clock right now.

193
00:11:32,024 --> 00:11:35,661
Maybe he was told to kill her, to be
forgiven for running off with the gold.

194
00:11:35,728 --> 00:11:39,265
I just felt refreshed,
don't bring up such heavy topics.

195
00:11:39,331 --> 00:11:41,801
And then he was betrayed
and killed by Togo.

196
00:11:43,636 --> 00:11:46,872
Did the gold bars destroy the relationship
the four of them had?

197
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:51,644
We just have to find
one of the people in that photo.

198
00:11:52,578 --> 00:11:53,646
What about Saki Yokokura?

199
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:56,749
She vanished.

200
00:11:57,516 --> 00:12:01,387
<i>When First Division went, the room</i>
<i>was ransacked, and bloodstains were found.</i>

201
00:12:01,454 --> 00:12:03,289
-Check the security cameras.
-Yes.

202
00:12:05,024 --> 00:12:07,226
That might be Togo's doing as well.

203
00:12:08,260 --> 00:12:11,263
Did he kidnap her
to find out where the gold is?

204
00:12:12,331 --> 00:12:15,234
It's too early to be certain,
but you should hurry up and go.

205
00:12:15,301 --> 00:12:16,235
What?

206
00:12:17,369 --> 00:12:18,437
To Akita.

207
00:12:20,372 --> 00:12:22,007
What a pain.

208
00:12:24,009 --> 00:12:25,444
Mogi, gyoza.

209
00:12:25,511 --> 00:12:26,512
For two.

210
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:33,586
What happened to the man named Tsuda?

211
00:12:37,656 --> 00:12:38,924
He died of an illness.

212
00:12:40,826 --> 00:12:43,395
We didn't get
any info out of him in the end.

213
00:12:46,966 --> 00:12:47,800
I see.

214
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:48,934
But…

215
00:12:51,370 --> 00:12:52,438
it's not over yet.

216
00:12:55,741 --> 00:12:56,675
Minoru.

217
00:12:57,843 --> 00:12:58,978
I'll leave it to you.

218
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:01,747
Sure.

219
00:13:11,657 --> 00:13:14,894
KARASHIMA

220
00:13:20,232 --> 00:13:21,333
Welcome.

221
00:13:22,701 --> 00:13:23,869
It has been a while.

222
00:13:25,971 --> 00:13:26,939
Minoru?

223
00:13:47,126 --> 00:13:48,460
Here you go.

224
00:13:49,595 --> 00:13:52,798
Makoto had to go to Akita
on a sudden business trip.

225
00:13:53,365 --> 00:13:56,202
I see. Sounds like he's doing well.

226
00:13:56,735 --> 00:13:58,838
Fumi, how have you been since then?

227
00:13:59,371 --> 00:14:04,643
I underwent surgery,
and steadily continued with my rehab…

228
00:14:04,710 --> 00:14:07,246
Is that how you're able to take
photos of mountains again?

229
00:14:07,746 --> 00:14:09,615
I'm still full of energy, you know.

230
00:14:10,115 --> 00:14:11,951
I'm going climbing again next week.

231
00:14:14,486 --> 00:14:15,788
Back then,

232
00:14:17,056 --> 00:14:19,491
I had almost given up,
thinking it was impossible.

233
00:14:20,426 --> 00:14:24,129
It’s amazing that you’re even holding
a solo exhibition now.

234
00:14:24,196 --> 00:14:26,632
Oh, you know a lot.

235
00:14:26,699 --> 00:14:28,467
I looked you up online.

236
00:14:37,309 --> 00:14:38,510
So, what is it today?

237
00:14:40,846 --> 00:14:42,348
You wanted to ask me something?

238
00:14:46,518 --> 00:14:48,921
You know a man
named Yuji Tsuda, don't you?

239
00:14:49,822 --> 00:14:50,689
Tsuda?

240
00:14:51,624 --> 00:14:54,493
He used to write nonfiction books.

241
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,794
An author.

242
00:14:55,861 --> 00:14:57,863
YUJI TSUDA
VOICES OF THE DEAD

243
00:14:57,930 --> 00:15:02,268
I don't know anyone like that.

244
00:15:02,334 --> 00:15:05,170
But he had your number, Fumi.

245
00:15:06,205 --> 00:15:07,139
Mine?

246
00:15:08,974 --> 00:15:10,242
Before the incident,

247
00:15:11,110 --> 00:15:13,612
did this man ever visit you?

248
00:15:19,285 --> 00:15:20,586
I'm sorry.

249
00:15:21,887 --> 00:15:25,391
Back then, I avoided meeting people.

250
00:15:36,802 --> 00:15:38,437
It's nice to see you again.

251
00:15:41,307 --> 00:15:43,442
Darling, this is Minoru.

252
00:15:43,509 --> 00:15:45,711
You know, from the Tagusaris.

253
00:15:53,018 --> 00:15:55,921
Excuse me, could I ask you
a few questions?

254
00:16:00,492 --> 00:16:03,629
He hasn't been feeling well lately.

255
00:16:05,464 --> 00:16:07,466
I'm sorry, Minoru.

256
00:16:14,306 --> 00:16:18,410
-Want to call the Japan Auto Federation?
-You idiot. How can the police call JAF?

257
00:16:20,179 --> 00:16:21,480
This will take some time.

258
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:24,383
Is it close by?

259
00:16:24,450 --> 00:16:25,751
Right there.

260
00:16:25,818 --> 00:16:29,188
But Asami Town is a big place.

261
00:16:29,254 --> 00:16:31,590
We can't do much with just that photo.

262
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:35,227
I'm sure he didn't want to go home,

263
00:16:35,294 --> 00:16:37,863
so he would be looking
for a place to stay nearby.

264
00:16:37,930 --> 00:16:39,298
Like a park?

265
00:16:39,798 --> 00:16:40,799
He won't be outside.

266
00:16:40,866 --> 00:16:43,602
-He would be caught immediately.
-Oh, right.

267
00:16:44,937 --> 00:16:48,474
The best place would be
somewhere he can get a meal

268
00:16:48,540 --> 00:16:50,809
even if he doesn't have money.

269
00:16:51,744 --> 00:16:53,979
I think I know a place like that.

270
00:16:56,615 --> 00:16:58,150
CHILDREN'S CANTEEN

271
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:01,887
This is definitely the place.

272
00:17:05,324 --> 00:17:07,826
Do these children look familiar to you?

273
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:12,197
How nostalgic.

274
00:17:12,264 --> 00:17:13,432
Do you know them?

275
00:17:13,499 --> 00:17:17,236
Yeah. All four of them
had a lot of trouble with their parents.

276
00:17:17,736 --> 00:17:21,440
They moved from place to place
and came here around the same time.

277
00:17:21,507 --> 00:17:23,041
Were they close?

278
00:17:23,108 --> 00:17:26,078
They were always together
when they were here.

279
00:17:26,812 --> 00:17:29,515
<i>They often talked about</i>

280
00:17:30,015 --> 00:17:32,584
<i>how they wanted to open</i>
<i>a shop together someday.</i>

281
00:17:32,651 --> 00:17:34,219
<i>They wanted children like them,</i>

282
00:17:34,787 --> 00:17:37,689
<i>who were facing various hardships,</i>
<i>to be able to come there.</i>

283
00:17:41,460 --> 00:17:43,729
Are you in contact with those four?

284
00:17:43,796 --> 00:17:45,464
No, not now.

285
00:17:46,532 --> 00:17:50,235
But Yuzuru stops by every now and then.

286
00:17:50,302 --> 00:17:51,870
Is it Yuzuru Togo?

287
00:17:52,571 --> 00:17:55,574
No, it's Yoshimoto. Yuzuru Yoshimoto.

288
00:17:56,708 --> 00:17:58,444
Have you ever heard the name Togo?

289
00:17:59,311 --> 00:18:02,047
I don't think so…

290
00:18:02,114 --> 00:18:06,151
Then, do you know
where Yuzuru Yoshimoto is?

291
00:18:07,119 --> 00:18:10,622
Oh, he's been visiting
his mother's nursing home.

292
00:18:11,623 --> 00:18:15,260
That woman in the wheelchair
is Yuzuru Yoshimoto's mother.

293
00:18:15,327 --> 00:18:17,296
I heard she was ill…

294
00:18:17,830 --> 00:18:20,065
She has always had a chronic illness,

295
00:18:20,132 --> 00:18:23,001
and Yuzuru has been
caring for her until now.

296
00:18:25,971 --> 00:18:29,575
This nursing home looks awfully pricey.

297
00:18:45,190 --> 00:18:46,291
I'm home.

298
00:18:56,635 --> 00:18:57,536
A souvenir.

299
00:18:58,604 --> 00:19:01,473
-Isn't it just from a convenience store?
-One in Akita!

300
00:19:01,540 --> 00:19:02,641
They're all the same.

301
00:19:03,275 --> 00:19:06,145
I even found the gummies you like!

302
00:19:09,181 --> 00:19:10,449
How was Fumi?

303
00:19:15,988 --> 00:19:17,122
Was it no good?

304
00:19:19,925 --> 00:19:22,060
She hadn't been in contact with Tsuda.

305
00:19:23,428 --> 00:19:25,564
I couldn't talk
to the factory manager either.

306
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:34,606
Why was Tsuda looking into that factory?

307
00:19:36,041 --> 00:19:38,377
Does it have anything to do with the case?

308
00:19:39,978 --> 00:19:41,446
I have no idea at all.

309
00:19:44,416 --> 00:19:45,484
What about the key?

310
00:19:46,051 --> 00:19:48,554
They say it's used for lockers,
desk drawers, padlocks…

311
00:19:48,620 --> 00:19:50,889
<i>All sorts of things.</i>
<i>It's a very common type.</i>

312
00:19:52,824 --> 00:19:54,993
At this rate, even if we had 100 years…

313
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:57,963
What about Dad's desk?

314
00:20:00,532 --> 00:20:03,502
The drawer of that desk was always locked.

315
00:20:05,003 --> 00:20:06,038
Then…

316
00:20:06,772 --> 00:20:08,907
it might be related to the factory.

317
00:20:19,351 --> 00:20:23,121
Next week, I'll be going to Hida.

318
00:20:29,361 --> 00:20:30,529
It will be okay.

319
00:20:32,931 --> 00:20:35,734
You don't have to worry about a thing.

320
00:20:47,613 --> 00:20:48,914
How was Akita?

321
00:20:49,748 --> 00:20:51,883
The last of the four is Yuzuru Yoshimoto.

322
00:20:51,950 --> 00:20:53,318
It wasn't Togo.

323
00:20:53,385 --> 00:20:54,219
What?

324
00:20:54,286 --> 00:20:55,988
Togo is likely the mastermind.

325
00:20:57,456 --> 00:21:00,459
Probably chased down the four
who ran off with the gold.

326
00:21:00,525 --> 00:21:02,761
Then, isn't Yoshimoto in danger?

327
00:21:03,262 --> 00:21:04,997
Yoshimoto also lives in Kanagawa,

328
00:21:05,063 --> 00:21:07,399
and the police are currently
staking out his home.

329
00:21:07,466 --> 00:21:10,669
They plan to wait until morning,
then take him into custody.

330
00:21:14,873 --> 00:21:15,874
But…

331
00:21:17,442 --> 00:21:19,177
maybe we should've left them alone.

332
00:21:20,579 --> 00:21:21,613
Why?

333
00:21:22,180 --> 00:21:24,049
Yoshimoto is a young caregiver,

334
00:21:24,916 --> 00:21:27,552
and Yokokura's father was in debt.

335
00:21:32,457 --> 00:21:35,627
They must've been desperate to survive.

336
00:21:36,862 --> 00:21:38,063
Even as kids.

337
00:21:44,403 --> 00:21:45,337
I suppose so.

338
00:21:55,814 --> 00:21:58,717
No one came to visit Yoshimoto.

339
00:22:00,686 --> 00:22:04,189
Togo isn't showing up either.

340
00:22:06,325 --> 00:22:08,660
I wonder if Saki Yokokura is okay?

341
00:22:09,761 --> 00:22:12,764
First Division is chasing it,
but hasn't found her yet.

342
00:22:12,831 --> 00:22:14,666
The apartment's security camera?

343
00:22:15,233 --> 00:22:17,569
Apparently, the whole
camera unit was taken.

344
00:22:22,107 --> 00:22:24,810
The four of them
all ran to Kanagawa, only for this…

345
00:22:28,280 --> 00:22:30,682
It's because they were stupid
and robbed people.

346
00:22:34,886 --> 00:22:35,821
He's out.

347
00:22:45,764 --> 00:22:47,599
You're Yuzuru Yoshimoto, right?

348
00:22:49,901 --> 00:22:51,436
Guess I don't even need to ask.

349
00:22:53,171 --> 00:22:55,107
Please come with us to the station.

350
00:22:55,173 --> 00:22:56,575
I was deceived.

351
00:22:58,076 --> 00:22:59,311
What do you mean by that?

352
00:23:00,078 --> 00:23:02,247
Saki called me.

353
00:23:02,314 --> 00:23:03,915
<i>The four of us will steal gold.</i>

354
00:23:04,583 --> 00:23:07,452
I was invited by a man named Togo.
He's the mastermind.

355
00:23:07,519 --> 00:23:11,356
He said the owner just wants to pretend
the gold was stolen, for tax purposes.

356
00:23:12,224 --> 00:23:14,726
Togo said the police
wouldn't even chase us.

357
00:23:16,628 --> 00:23:18,330
It's a fake robbery!

358
00:23:18,864 --> 00:23:22,434
The reward was 300,000 yen per person.

359
00:23:23,235 --> 00:23:24,236
What?

360
00:23:25,370 --> 00:23:27,406
You would commit robbery
for such a small amount?

361
00:23:28,573 --> 00:23:32,210
We didn't think we would get caught.

362
00:23:32,277 --> 00:23:34,279
And for us, that was enough.

363
00:23:35,881 --> 00:23:37,649
With 300,000 yen,

364
00:23:39,317 --> 00:23:41,586
I could hire a caregiver for my mother.

365
00:23:43,789 --> 00:23:45,290
Even if only for a short time,

366
00:23:45,991 --> 00:23:48,059
I could finally be free.

367
00:23:49,761 --> 00:23:54,132
In reality, you ended up being chased
by the police and Togo.

368
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:57,302
We had no choice but to run!

369
00:24:00,939 --> 00:24:02,908
Hey, Kudo.

370
00:24:10,749 --> 00:24:12,050
When that happens,

371
00:24:13,151 --> 00:24:14,386
you turn yourself in.

372
00:24:16,988 --> 00:24:17,889
Let's go.

373
00:24:38,510 --> 00:24:39,611
Thank you.

374
00:24:41,980 --> 00:24:45,016
After fleeing from Akita,
they turned the gold into cash.

375
00:24:45,650 --> 00:24:49,221
It seems there was
an unlicensed pawnshop in Yokohama.

376
00:24:50,021 --> 00:24:52,691
They each took 100 million
to pay off debts.

377
00:24:52,757 --> 00:24:54,626
or put their parents in facilities.

378
00:24:55,193 --> 00:24:57,829
They were finally liberated
from their parents.

379
00:24:58,630 --> 00:25:01,299
And Togo deceived those four?

380
00:25:03,134 --> 00:25:05,270
Can we trace Togo
through Yuzuru Yoshimoto?

381
00:25:05,804 --> 00:25:06,638
No.

382
00:25:06,705 --> 00:25:09,674
He says he never met him
or even contacted him.

383
00:25:10,876 --> 00:25:15,881
So in the end, the only connection
is Saki Yokokura, who was kidnapped.

384
00:25:18,083 --> 00:25:20,018
-Thank you!
-Thanks for the meal.

385
00:25:25,257 --> 00:25:27,225
Oh, what do you want, Haruko?

386
00:25:27,292 --> 00:25:28,293
A beer, please.

387
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:29,194
Sure thing.

388
00:25:30,395 --> 00:25:32,197
I heard from Minoru.

389
00:25:32,831 --> 00:25:34,299
He said Tsuda is dead.

390
00:25:35,066 --> 00:25:38,436
He said, they didn't get
anything out of him in the end.

391
00:25:40,338 --> 00:25:41,172
Yeah.

392
00:25:44,409 --> 00:25:45,243
Here.

393
00:25:45,310 --> 00:25:47,178
This is on the house.

394
00:25:47,812 --> 00:25:50,181
Wow, how nostalgic.

395
00:25:50,248 --> 00:25:52,250
Mogi's fried rice!

396
00:25:53,018 --> 00:25:55,720
Do you remember it? Minoru’s birthday.

397
00:25:56,321 --> 00:25:57,589
How could I forget?

398
00:25:58,690 --> 00:26:01,226
<i>I put candles in the fried rice.</i>

399
00:26:02,260 --> 00:26:04,529
<i>How did you ever think of that?</i>

400
00:26:04,596 --> 00:26:06,531
<i>I just wanted to do something for him.</i>

401
00:26:06,598 --> 00:26:09,701
At that time, we couldn't afford
to buy a cake.

402
00:26:10,302 --> 00:26:13,838
But, he looked so incredibly happy.

403
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:19,010
Back then, they were like
ordinary kids you would see anywhere.

404
00:26:24,516 --> 00:26:26,585
But I suppose I was wrong.

405
00:26:28,887 --> 00:26:31,790
If I had stayed close to them
and supported them,

406
00:26:31,856 --> 00:26:33,892
they might have had a different future.

407
00:26:35,427 --> 00:26:38,663
By now, Minoru would have become
a forensic scientist, and Makoto…

408
00:26:38,730 --> 00:26:39,998
What are you saying?

409
00:26:40,699 --> 00:26:42,601
You supported them well.

410
00:26:49,674 --> 00:26:53,111
I hope one day,
we can laugh like that again.

411
00:26:55,914 --> 00:26:56,848
Yeah.

412
00:27:02,687 --> 00:27:04,155
I knew I would find you here.

413
00:27:07,592 --> 00:27:10,295
I went to the shop
to try to sell you this.

414
00:27:10,862 --> 00:27:14,499
VOICES OF THE DEAD

415
00:27:18,637 --> 00:27:19,904
Is this Tsuda's?

416
00:27:21,473 --> 00:27:23,308
I don't need it anymore.

417
00:27:26,845 --> 00:27:29,481
You mean there's another culprit
besides Tsuda?

418
00:27:30,081 --> 00:27:31,750
Isn't there anything you can remember?

419
00:27:38,423 --> 00:27:40,959
<i>You're the only one who saw the culprit.</i>

420
00:27:43,762 --> 00:27:45,130
It was dark,

421
00:27:45,964 --> 00:27:48,199
and they were wearing a hood and a mask.

422
00:27:50,168 --> 00:27:51,136
I'm sorry.

423
00:27:51,936 --> 00:27:53,438
I've asked you so many times.

424
00:27:56,541 --> 00:27:58,510
So you have no clues at all.

425
00:27:59,310 --> 00:28:00,145
No…

426
00:28:03,014 --> 00:28:04,315
There's one thing left.

427
00:28:18,063 --> 00:28:19,130
Haruko.

428
00:28:20,699 --> 00:28:22,333
Introduce me to a good pawnshop.

429
00:28:24,035 --> 00:28:26,204
If you're looking for a fight,
I'll fight you.

430
00:28:26,271 --> 00:28:28,606
Do you know a shop
in Yokohama called Suiren-do?

431
00:28:34,446 --> 00:28:36,648
That place was flagged by police,

432
00:28:36,715 --> 00:28:39,250
and its owner fled back
to his country six months ago.

433
00:28:39,317 --> 00:28:42,220
That's why I want to know
about shops that "cross the line."

434
00:28:43,922 --> 00:28:47,025
You can't keep gold bars
with a trail on them forever.

435
00:28:47,692 --> 00:28:49,561
Togo must want to cash them out.

436
00:28:53,465 --> 00:28:55,967
There's no time. Hurry up.

437
00:28:58,203 --> 00:28:59,904
I can't tell you anything, Makoto.

438
00:29:00,638 --> 00:29:01,539
What?

439
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:04,909
Sorry, but I can't sell out my colleagues.

440
00:29:04,976 --> 00:29:06,277
Look into it yourselves.

441
00:29:06,344 --> 00:29:07,879
Haruko.

442
00:29:07,946 --> 00:29:10,215
We have our own rules over here!

443
00:29:16,821 --> 00:29:19,457
YUGO HIRANAKA MURDER CASE AUTOPSY RESULTS

444
00:29:19,524 --> 00:29:22,393
Are these the forensics results
for Yugo Hiranaka?

445
00:29:22,460 --> 00:29:23,495
Yes.

446
00:29:24,229 --> 00:29:26,364
I read Yuzuru Yoshimoto's statement.

447
00:29:26,431 --> 00:29:28,967
He says Hiranaka had no prior
connection with Togo.

448
00:29:29,801 --> 00:29:31,236
If they weren't acquaintances,

449
00:29:31,302 --> 00:29:33,438
the footprints
in the parking lot bother me.

450
00:29:34,005 --> 00:29:35,306
Footprints?

451
00:29:35,373 --> 00:29:38,510
Because it was raining, only the
footprints in the perimeter remained,

452
00:29:39,244 --> 00:29:43,515
but Togo's stride is clearly shorter
than Hiranaka's.

453
00:29:43,581 --> 00:29:44,482
What?

454
00:29:44,983 --> 00:29:47,919
Please send Togo's security footage
for gait analysis.

455
00:29:47,986 --> 00:29:50,588
But we can't identify
without a subject for comparison.

456
00:29:50,655 --> 00:29:51,990
I don't mind.

457
00:29:52,056 --> 00:29:54,325
I just want to know more about their gait.

458
00:29:54,392 --> 00:29:55,360
On it.

459
00:29:56,294 --> 00:29:59,364
KAWADA PAWNSHOP

460
00:30:00,165 --> 00:30:02,400
He might have already cashed it in.

461
00:30:05,069 --> 00:30:08,640
It has been three days
since Togo ran off with Hiranaka's gold.

462
00:30:08,706 --> 00:30:12,911
Even if Yokokura still had her gold left,
she was kidnapped two days ago.

463
00:30:20,952 --> 00:30:21,920
Hello?

464
00:30:22,420 --> 00:30:24,355
<i>That shop wasn't it, huh?</i>

465
00:30:25,790 --> 00:30:27,992
If you're messing with me, I'm hanging up.

466
00:30:28,059 --> 00:30:31,196
<i>It seems a certain pawnshop</i>
<i>just received some gold bars.</i>

467
00:30:31,863 --> 00:30:32,530
What?

468
00:30:33,498 --> 00:30:36,100
I asked shops I know to contact me
if something comes up.

469
00:30:37,435 --> 00:30:39,737
Connections are important, you know.

470
00:30:40,872 --> 00:30:43,041
If you don't hurry, you won't catch them.

471
00:30:43,107 --> 00:30:46,110
The shop's name is Kiho in Yokohama.

472
00:30:49,614 --> 00:30:50,515
Drive!

473
00:30:50,582 --> 00:30:51,616
Yes.

474
00:30:58,957 --> 00:31:00,959
I wonder if Togo is still at the shop.

475
00:31:02,126 --> 00:31:02,961
What's wrong?

476
00:31:03,528 --> 00:31:05,496
The variance in the depths of the wounds…

477
00:31:05,563 --> 00:31:08,366
-It's due to a lack of muscle strength.
<i>-What?</i>

478
00:31:08,433 --> 00:31:11,502
After analyzing Togo's gait
on the camera footage,

479
00:31:11,569 --> 00:31:13,705
there is an approximately 90% probability…

480
00:31:15,673 --> 00:31:17,208
that Togo is a woman.

481
00:31:22,013 --> 00:31:23,915
KIHO PAWNSHOP

482
00:31:26,517 --> 00:31:27,552
Mr. Tagusari?

483
00:31:43,735 --> 00:31:44,702
Yokokura.

484
00:31:52,744 --> 00:31:53,778
Oh, no…

485
00:31:54,345 --> 00:31:55,246
I'm busted, aren't I?

486
00:31:58,917 --> 00:32:01,319
I went to the trouble
of cutting my own arm, too.

487
00:32:08,259 --> 00:32:09,627
Can I have a smoke?

488
00:32:10,428 --> 00:32:11,396
Since it's my last.

489
00:32:19,437 --> 00:32:21,239
You're Togo, aren't you?

490
00:32:27,245 --> 00:32:28,613
Togo was…

491
00:32:31,883 --> 00:32:34,385
the debt collector
who used to come to our house.

492
00:32:35,386 --> 00:32:36,888
Every single day…

493
00:32:37,522 --> 00:32:40,625
he would bang on the door,
saying, "Pay back the money!"

494
00:32:42,060 --> 00:32:46,698
That voice got stuck in my ears,
so I ended up using his name.

495
00:32:50,935 --> 00:32:52,437
So from the beginning,

496
00:32:53,204 --> 00:32:55,340
there never was a man named Togo.

497
00:32:58,910 --> 00:33:01,312
Aiko Mizusawa realized that, didn't she?

498
00:33:03,348 --> 00:33:04,449
That girl…

499
00:33:05,416 --> 00:33:09,320
for someone so unfriendly,
her intuition was sharp.

500
00:33:11,689 --> 00:33:12,590
Hey.

501
00:33:12,657 --> 00:33:13,858
Togo…

502
00:33:14,892 --> 00:33:16,627
doesn't actually exist, does he?

503
00:33:17,628 --> 00:33:18,463
What?

504
00:33:18,529 --> 00:33:21,733
Saki, you made him up.

505
00:33:24,635 --> 00:33:27,238
<i>I tried to make it seem</i>
<i>like a misunderstanding.</i>

506
00:33:27,805 --> 00:33:31,709
<i>I told Yugo that Aiko</i>
<i>was planning to betray us.</i>

507
00:33:31,776 --> 00:33:34,645
You mean Aiko is trying
to turn herself in?

508
00:33:35,380 --> 00:33:37,081
If we threaten her a little,

509
00:33:38,082 --> 00:33:40,318
Aiko might change her mind.

510
00:33:40,952 --> 00:33:43,554
<i>We thought if we set the fire</i>
<i>while I was at work,</i>

511
00:33:44,255 --> 00:33:47,325
<i>we could make Aiko believe Togo existed.</i>

512
00:33:49,460 --> 00:33:52,697
<i>I never imagined she would be home.</i>

513
00:33:53,431 --> 00:33:54,599
<i>The police are here.</i>

514
00:33:54,665 --> 00:33:56,134
<i>We can't run anymore.</i>

515
00:33:56,934 --> 00:33:59,904
That was an accident. It's not your fault.

516
00:33:59,971 --> 00:34:01,606
<i>I'm going to turn myself in.</i>

517
00:34:01,672 --> 00:34:03,641
<i>I have to tell them</i>
<i>I thought Aiko wasn't--</i>

518
00:34:03,708 --> 00:34:04,642
Wait a minute.

519
00:34:06,611 --> 00:34:08,946
I'm going to the police
to tell them everything.

520
00:34:11,582 --> 00:34:13,785
<i>There was no turning back anymore.</i>

521
00:34:24,862 --> 00:34:26,831
I don't particularly have any regrets.

522
00:34:45,216 --> 00:34:46,517
I wish I had been born

523
00:34:48,086 --> 00:34:49,921
into a house like that.

524
00:34:52,957 --> 00:34:55,293
The children at that canteen

525
00:34:56,360 --> 00:34:58,896
all needed money.

526
00:35:03,734 --> 00:35:05,670
We had to either live without dreams

527
00:35:07,505 --> 00:35:09,540
or do bad stuff.

528
00:35:13,044 --> 00:35:14,078
But…

529
00:35:15,847 --> 00:35:18,082
if you have money, everything changes.

530
00:35:19,317 --> 00:35:20,885
As long as you have money…

531
00:35:21,686 --> 00:35:23,154
And how did that turn out?

532
00:35:26,023 --> 00:35:27,558
Once you got the money,

533
00:35:28,860 --> 00:35:30,228
did it go as you planned?

534
00:35:33,431 --> 00:35:35,166
The reason I turned out like this

535
00:35:36,767 --> 00:35:38,569
is all because of my parents.

536
00:35:42,673 --> 00:35:44,175
It’s all your fault.

537
00:35:45,977 --> 00:35:48,613
"If not for you,
I wouldn't have suffered like this."

538
00:35:52,483 --> 00:35:56,220
All worthless parents
say that to their children.

539
00:35:58,256 --> 00:35:59,423
But…

540
00:35:59,490 --> 00:36:03,427
because those kids don't want to trouble
their parents, they can't ask for help.

541
00:36:06,364 --> 00:36:09,167
Even when told,
"I wish I had never given birth to you,"

542
00:36:09,834 --> 00:36:11,769
they still can't abandon their parents.

543
00:36:17,475 --> 00:36:18,943
It’s pathetic, isn't it?

544
00:36:38,596 --> 00:36:40,364
She confessed to the crimes.

545
00:36:41,165 --> 00:36:42,066
I see.

546
00:36:44,769 --> 00:36:45,803
That vehicle…

547
00:36:49,407 --> 00:36:53,211
It was delivered
to Aiko Mizusawa's home today.

548
00:36:54,745 --> 00:36:55,780
Mizusawa's?

549
00:36:56,347 --> 00:36:57,582
According to the dealer,

550
00:36:58,115 --> 00:37:00,785
she talked about how
she was going to start

551
00:37:00,851 --> 00:37:02,887
a shop with her friends.

552
00:37:05,423 --> 00:37:07,892
And she seemed so happy.

553
00:37:12,663 --> 00:37:13,931
Mizusawa

554
00:37:14,765 --> 00:37:18,169
hadn't spent a single yen of that gold.

555
00:37:20,204 --> 00:37:22,240
The money you spent,

556
00:37:23,641 --> 00:37:26,077
she probably intended
to earn and pay it back.

557
00:37:29,180 --> 00:37:31,082
With the dream you had back then.

558
00:37:40,157 --> 00:37:43,327
When we grow up,
let's run a shop together.

559
00:37:43,394 --> 00:37:44,629
What kind of shop?

560
00:37:45,296 --> 00:37:48,399
A place like this,
where all kinds of kids can come.

561
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:50,067
That sounds good!

562
00:37:56,607 --> 00:37:59,277
It really would've been better
if Togo existed.

563
00:38:13,457 --> 00:38:14,392
Let's go.

564
00:38:30,241 --> 00:38:32,610
You seem curious, so I'll tell you.

565
00:38:33,744 --> 00:38:37,048
When I was a child,
my father chose another woman,

566
00:38:37,114 --> 00:38:38,783
and my parents divorced.

567
00:38:39,817 --> 00:38:42,520
She was flashier
and more beautiful than my mother.

568
00:38:43,854 --> 00:38:48,359
After that, my mother started obsessively
buying clothes and makeup,

569
00:38:48,426 --> 00:38:50,561
and when the money in our house ran out…

570
00:38:52,830 --> 00:38:56,000
She began to force me to shoplift.

571
00:39:01,739 --> 00:39:03,341
If I had made one wrong move,

572
00:39:05,176 --> 00:39:07,411
I could have been one of those four.

573
00:39:12,783 --> 00:39:13,851
But…

574
00:39:14,852 --> 00:39:17,922
your family environment
doesn't decide everything.

575
00:39:20,191 --> 00:39:24,595
The path you walk is up to you.

576
00:39:33,738 --> 00:39:34,705
Hey.

577
00:39:34,772 --> 00:39:36,273
Say something.

578
00:39:38,743 --> 00:39:40,244
I don't have anything to say.

579
00:39:43,581 --> 00:39:44,548
I know that

580
00:39:46,350 --> 00:39:47,985
you won't make a mistake again.

581
00:39:58,295 --> 00:39:59,130
Hey.

582
00:40:00,731 --> 00:40:02,466
What was our dad like?

583
00:40:04,235 --> 00:40:05,236
Was he decent?

584
00:40:07,037 --> 00:40:11,075
Dad was hungover
for most of his mornings off.

585
00:40:12,810 --> 00:40:14,445
He did smell like booze.

586
00:40:15,479 --> 00:40:18,282
One time, Mom even poured
hot water on him to wake him up.

587
00:40:18,816 --> 00:40:20,151
Oh, yes, that happened.

588
00:40:20,217 --> 00:40:21,786
You have a good memory!

589
00:40:24,155 --> 00:40:25,956
I've forgotten quite a bit.

590
00:40:28,092 --> 00:40:30,428
I'm forgetting more and more things.

591
00:40:33,831 --> 00:40:34,999
It can't be helped.

592
00:40:35,566 --> 00:40:37,001
You were only five back then.

593
00:40:43,507 --> 00:40:45,476
I'm jealous of you, Makoto.

594
00:41:17,308 --> 00:41:19,410
It's no use. It doesn't fit.

595
00:41:20,611 --> 00:41:22,446
What’s inside?

596
00:42:24,508 --> 00:42:27,578
Few dads would make their kids
something like this.

597
00:42:34,518 --> 00:42:35,486
Minoru?

598
00:42:37,054 --> 00:42:38,322
Makoto.

599
00:42:38,389 --> 00:42:39,757
You saw it from here, right?

600
00:42:39,823 --> 00:42:41,191
I don't care about that!

601
00:42:41,892 --> 00:42:43,494
Let me hear your side. Hey!

602
00:42:43,561 --> 00:42:45,763
-I'm busy, go home.
-No!

603
00:42:47,131 --> 00:42:48,198
That guy…

604
00:42:49,567 --> 00:42:51,802
I wonder what he wanted to hear from Dad?

605
00:42:57,508 --> 00:42:59,376
I'll try going to Fumi's too.

606
00:42:59,977 --> 00:43:01,879
I'll talk to the factory manager too.

607
00:43:09,987 --> 00:43:10,821
What’s wrong?

608
00:43:47,791 --> 00:43:48,859
If we investigate further,

609
00:43:48,926 --> 00:43:50,894
<i>we might find out things</i>
<i>we don't want to know.</i>

610
00:43:50,961 --> 00:43:53,063
<i>Why was Dad complicit</i>
<i>in something like that?</i>

611
00:43:53,130 --> 00:43:54,331
I killed them.

612
00:43:54,898 --> 00:43:55,966
<i>He won't speak at all.</i>

613
00:43:56,033 --> 00:43:57,735
<i>You have a hidden agenda, don't you?</i>

614
00:43:57,801 --> 00:43:58,936
Subtitle translation by: Nix S.
